title: For Sale:  FS/FT: AR-15 Faux "Dissipator" | $600
postcontent: This is a faux "dissipator" AR-15. For those of you who aren't familiar, "dissipator" is a term for A1/A2 variant AR-15s that had the barrel chopped at 16", making them more handy than their 20" ancestors while retaining the nice long sight radius of the rifle length gas system. The downside was that having the gas port so close to the muzzle led to some performance issues. Manufacturers today produce a faux dissipator, which is a 16" mid gas barrel with a low profile gas block, and a pinned rifle-length FSB, so you get the best of both worlds.I built this gun a couple years ago and I've put about 500 rounds through it without any problems- runs like a top. I started with a really nice barrel and built the rest around it.-Daniel Defense 16" mid-gas CHF chrome lined barrel 1:7 twist, with a professionally pinned Daniel Defense F-marked front sight base (done by Weapon Outfitters)-Daniel Defense Phosphate BCG-Anderson upper and lower receiver and associated parts kits-Aero Precision A2 carry handle rear sight-Mil spec A2 buttstock (I've got a front sight adjustment tool and boresnake stowed in there that comes with the gun)-Daniel Defense pistol grip with integral trigger guard-Daniel Defense VFG-Magpul M-Lok rifle length handguard-Magpul M-Lok hand stopI'd like to get $600 for it, face to face. Also considering trades, mostly interested 9mm handguns. Have CPL.

title: For Sale:  Spyderco Navaja
postcontent: Up for sale is a Spyderco Navaja in very good condition. These knives were discontinued by Spydero years ago and they have become hard to acquire collectors pieces. The carraca mechanism works just fine on this one, unlike many others that are listed on ebay. It also has the original box and paperwork. Features premium s30v steel with a 3.8" blade that I have given a custom 20 degree micro bevel and 15 degree back bevel as recomended by Spyderco. This helps maintain the edge much longer than a thinner edge, but allows for more efficient cutting at the same time with the thinner back bevel. Only wear is on the left bolster, and it is some very minor and light scuffs. People are asking between 200-400 dollar for this knife on ebay and you cannot find them in stores. Face to face cash transaction only. "First noted in 15th century Spain among Gypsies and Gitanos, the Navaja folding knife was used for work, utility and protection. They’re shaped similarly to barbering razors or novacula, meaning razor in Spanish. Modern definition categorizes it as a modified clip-point with an unsharpened concave spine swedge. Unique to the Navaja is the Carraca or ratcheting sound produced when opening or closing the blade. It announces the knife’s presence and is believed to raise anxiety and anticipation, deterring criminals. Ed Schempp’s modernized Navaja has a carbon fiber handle, stainless steel bolsters, pocket clip and the Carraca (ratcheting sound), maintaining the mystique of the Navaja."
